#: ../../source/manpages/nsd.rst:19
msgid ""
":command:`NSD` is a complete implementation of an  authoritative DNS "
"nameserver. Upon startup, :command:`NSD` will read the database specified"
" with :option:`-f` ``database`` argument and put itself into background "
"and answers queries on port 53 or a different port specified with "
":option:`-p` ``port`` option. The database is created if it does not "
"exist. By default, :command:`NSD` will bind to all local interfaces "
"available. Use the :option:`-a` ``ip-address[@port]`` option to specify a"
" single particular interface address to be bound. If this  option is "
"given more than once, :command:`NSD` will bind its UDP and TCP sockets to"
" all the specified ip-addresses separately. If IPv6 is enabled when "
":command:`NSD` is compiled an IPv6 address can also be specified."
msgstr ""

